10100001.m_mItemDesc3: "One of the three origins of Alchemy. This yellow mineral is extremely flammable, releasing an intense scent when burned. It never fails to stir an alchemist's imagination about souls."

10100002.m_mItemDesc3: "A transparent substance that purifies all turbid liquids with its touch. It seems to embody the serene power of order."

10100003.m_mItemDesc3: "One of the three origins of Alchemy. This white crystal is the cornerstone—containing the power of purification, essential for exorcism rituals."

10100004.m_mItemDesc3: "A green gem, said to be the eye of a mythical bird. Alchemists believe that it holds the power to heal and revive the dead."

10100005.m_mItemDesc3: "A silver-white metal capable of refining other metals by removing impurities. Alchemists call it the "wolf" for the howling sound it makes during smelting."

10100006.m_mItemDesc3: "Seemingly harmless, this white, crystal-like substance can be transformed into corrosive acid or explosive compounds. Handle with caution."

10100007.m_mItemDesc3: "A hard, grey metal that is abundant in nature and easy to forge. A crucial material in the Church's Silver Blood Trial."

10100008.m_mItemDesc3: "The origin of Alchemy. This heavy grey metal is disordered—like the nature of the primordial universe itself."

10100009.m_mItemDesc3: "Known as "the unmelted ice" for its translucent, prismatic structure. Said to reveal glimpses of the future, it's a perfect medium for diviners to commune with spirits."

10100010.m_mItemDesc3: "A deep grayish ore, symbolizing death through its lethal toxicity. Yet to alchemists, this very power of destruction holds the potential for new life."

10100011.m_mItemDesc3: "A reddish-brown metal that lasts much longer than iron, though it is less durable than gold or silver. It retains its noble luster through the wear of time."

10100012.m_mItemDesc3: "One of the three origins of Alchemy. This silver-like liquid substance is hailed by alchemists as the 'Source of Immortality.' Yet rumors speak of those who drank it meeting gruesome ends."

10100013.m_mItemDesc3: "A pristine metal with cleansing power. The Church crafts holy relics and armor with it to battle against heretics."

10100014.m_mItemDesc3: "A heavy yellow metal, sought by mortals as a symbol of wealth, and revered by alchemists as their ultimate pursuit."

10100015.m_mItemDesc3: "A rounded gem hidden in the ocean depths, known as the 'Moon of the Sea' for its pristine, silvery glow. Said to bestow purity and wisdom."

10100016.m_mItemDesc3: "A golden solid often used to craft candlesticks that dispel darkness. Some may coat their bodies with its cooled wax in pursuit of longevity."

10100017.m_mItemDesc3: "A golden resin often distilled into essence by alchemists. A single dab applied to the forehead is said to grant a glimpse of insight."

10100018.m_mItemDesc3: "A twisted root, said to release terrifying screams. Alchemists deem it a potent magical material."

10100019.m_mItemDesc3: "Fragrant leaves from an evergreen tree. They are said to inspire prophetic dreams and poetic revelation when placed beneath one's pillow."

10100020.m_mItemDesc3: "Sharp fangs, often crafted into amulets. Said to drain power from enemies when worn."

10100021.m_mItemDesc3: "A transparent sphere filled with liquid. Alchemists claim it holds the key to creating life—though some see it as the birth of Calamity."

10100022.m_mItemDesc3: "An eerie crimson liquid said to be distilled from Abel's blood. It grants immortality at the cost of one's humanity."

10100023.m_mItemDesc3: "A red sea creature believed to be the bones of the ocean god. It is said to protect sailors from storms and waves with the power of the sea."

10100024.m_mItemDesc3: "The antler of a stag. It shares a bond with nature and carries the essence of the changing seasons."

10100025.m_mItemDesc3: "A shed snakeskin, sought by alchemists for the secret of immortality. Fragile, yet it holds remarkable power of revival when used in potions."

10100026.m_mItemDesc3: "A tiny insect bearing divine revelation. God said, 'Let there be light,' and there was light. From that moment, light was separated from darkness."

10200001.m_mItemDesc3: "A dark, bitter liquid that keeps one alert through the night. Would likely fetch a good price among night watchmen and ascetics."
10200001.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 1"

10200003.m_mItemDesc2: "When using Basic ATK, all Melee units have a chance to deal DMG in a cone."
10200003.m_mItemDesc3: "A weapon that fits in the palm. When unfolded, it becomes a fan with razor edges. Favored by eastern assassins, it reaps souls in silence."

10200004.m_mItemDesc2: "Creates Blood Pools near all allied Melee Vassals. Enemies inside the Blood Pool take DMG, while nearby Vassal recovers HP."
10200004.m_mItemDesc3: "A syringe with silver spikes. In the hands of The Peace Council, it would be a perfect instrument for drawing blood."

10200005.m_mItemDesc2: "Enemies have a chance to explode upon death, dealing DMG to nearby enemies."
10200005.m_mItemDesc3: "A container filled with black powder brought from the east by the El Dorado. A single spark is enough to unleash earth-shattering power."

10200006.m_mItemDesc2: "A chance to trigger a chain lightning effect on up to 3 targets, upon hitting enemies with ranged Basic ATKs."
10200006.m_mItemDesc3:
"A glasswork device, handcrafted with care.
Someone once tried to trap light inside—only to catch a fleeting rainbow instead."
10200006.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 7"

10200007.m_mItemDesc2: "When Sorcerers and Enchanters perform Basic ATK, there is a chance to summon a Meteorite that deals AoE DMG in a random area."
10200007.m_mItemDesc3: "A flaming rock fell from the sky. Is it Aeon's divine punishment, or a harbinger of disaster?"
10200007.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 2"

10200008.m_mItemDesc2: "All Marksmen are accompanied by a Wooden Aerocraft."
10200008.m_mItemDesc3: "A peculiar wooden device that lifts one up in the sky. One shudders to think what eccentrics the Hermetic Order might make with it."

10200009.m_mItemDesc3: "A stone altar adorned with candlelight, surrounded by beast heads. Is it a magic circle, or a heretic's sacrifice?"
10200009.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 4"

10200010.m_mItemDesc3: "A peculiar device prone to sudden explosions. In the wrong hands, the consequences are unthinkable."
10200010.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 3"

10200013.m_mItemDesc2: "Periodically places a barrel at random locations on the field. The barrel explodes when enemies make contact."
10200013.m_mItemDesc3: "A barrel filled with the nectar of joy. A single taste of euphoria, enough to intoxicate and ease sleepless nights."
10200013.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 6"

10200017.m_mItemDesc2: "Periodically place an ice trap at random locations that continuously slow nearby enemies and deal DMG."
10200017.m_mItemDesc3: "A clay instrument with small holes. When the right tune is played, strange phenomena seem to awaken."
10200017.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 5"

10200020.m_mItemDesc2: "All melee units create a circling fireball that launches upon hitting an enemy, dealing DMG to enemies in its path."
10200020.m_mItemDesc3:
"A complex mechanical device.
Inspired by an engineer's nightmare, some speculated he dreamed of hellfire raining from the sky.
In fact, it was just a dream about complicated parabolic formulas."
10200020.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 8"

10300010.m_mItemDesc3: "A silver sword left at the convergence of realms. The blood crusted on its hilt speaks of Noah's glorious victories as the "Bloodborn hunter" for the Church. In another life, would he still suffer from doubt, or yearn for an unreachable homeland—even if he no longer dwelled in the shadow of the sun?"

10300020.m_mItemDesc3: "A shield left at the convergence of realms. Its twisted design was once hailed by the "great weaponsmith" Jestel as a work of rare artistry. In another life, would she still recall the tale of the Moonblessed, and share it with her kin?"

10300030.m_mItemDesc3: "A bouquet left at the convergence of realms. Planting carnations among piles of bones was the wish of Empousa, the "new leader of the family." In another life, would she wonder how fate might have shifted, had she dared venture into Starfall Valley that night?"

10300040.m_mItemDesc3: "Observation equipment left at the convergence of realms. "The observer of time," Aiona, has worn through thousands like it. In another life, would she abandon her obsession with the end of time—and consider leaving the Alita family to seek a different sky?"

10300050.m_mItemDesc3: "A flaming bow left at the convergence of realms. Its charred surface bears witness to the "new Bell Ringer" Setti’s mastery of fire. In another life, would she have questioned her teacher’s true intentions that night in Starfall Valley, after taking Agares's place?"

10300060.m_mItemDesc3: "Seafaring gourmet foods left at the convergence of realms. The writhing tentacles on the platter are trophies from Ami, "Captain of the El Dorado," taken from the deep. In another life, would she still yearn for the land while bound to the helm—or would the sea and storm, at last, feel like home?"

10300070.m_mItemDesc3: "Bones left at the convergence of realms. Precisely modified and fused with the body of Cecia, the "Ascendant." In another life, having refused to be her family's sacrifice, would she have found her true self in flesh and metal?"

10300080.m_mItemDesc3: "A music box left at the convergence of realms. The little girl dancing atop it glows like "Lady" Bella herself. In another life, as pure flesh and blood, would she care about if the puppet in the box had a soul?"

10300090.m_mItemDesc3: "A staff left at the convergence of realms. The snake coiled atop has guided countless lost souls with Cain, the "guide to the Other Side." In another life, when he walked the world of the living, would things have turned out differently for Cain had he finished that chess game at the Demon Banquet?"

10300100.m_mItemDesc3: "A torch left at the convergence of realms. Raising it was Agares's first act of feigned loyalty as "Dracula's follower." In another life, where he stands but one step from godhood, would he ever reminisce about the Manor of Eternal Flame?"

10300110.m_mItemDesc3: "Some bats forgotten by time and space, endlessly squabbling over food, carefree, like echoes of the newfound joy of Lamia, the "runaway." In another life, would she ever miss those petty battles at home after breaking free?"

10300120.m_mItemDesc3: "A sword forgotten by time and space, one that has purged countless heretics, bestowed upon Gilrain by the Church when he was chosen as the "Bell Ringer of Light." In another life, no longer shying away from the light, would he secretly long for a worthy adversary?"

10300130.m_mItemDesc3: "A gauntlet left at the convergence of realms. The wolf claws on it were the prized weapons of Hati. In another life, no longer the "warrior of Ganelon," would she simply wear the cloak her father made and visit the town for the blooming Wolfsbane?"

10300140.m_mItemDesc3: "Shears left at the convergence of realms. In the hands of Gilrain, the "castle gardener," it became a tool for shearing sheep and tending to flowers. In another life, where peace is his sole pursuit, would he ever truly quench his hunger for power?"

10300150.m_mItemDesc3: "A cloak left at the convergence of realms. These massive bat wings are a symbol of loyalty to Dracula as a "Bloodborn Elder." In another life, would Mass move on from that palace after turning her back on the family?"

10300160.m_mItemDesc3: "A pair of handwraps left at the convergence of realms. The rose pattern adorning them symbolizes the happy ending of "village girl" Ressa with her childhood sweetheart. In another life, would she ever realize how precious her simple life on Sunset Isle was?"

10300170.m_mItemDesc3: "Remains of beasts left at the convergence of realms. The precise cuts speak to the surgical mastery of the "bounty hunter" Darcias. In another life, would she look back on her pursuit of wealth as a quiet submission to a darker power?"

10300180.m_mItemDesc3: "A longsword left at the convergence of realms. Its unique design marks it as belonging to the second son of the Roland family—the Knight. In another life, freed from his fate as a Bell Ringer candidate, would Friedrich ever find his true calling?"

10300190.m_mItemDesc3: "Statues forgotten by time and space, this shield-like trinket bearing the crest of deities, handpicked by Theophane the "humble father" as a gift for his beloved daughter. In another life, would he simply savor the joy of family in a world untouched by war?"

10300200.m_mItemDesc3: "Snacks left at the convergence of realms. These black garlics were "tavern regular" Gadric's favorite delicacy during tavern nights with friends. In another life, would he have a lighter heart for such simple indulgences?"

10300210.m_mItemDesc3: "A violin left at the convergence of realms. Bizarrely shaped, yet it served "dark nursery composer" Acappella best in crafting her works. In another life, wandering the streets without a home, would she still yearn for a place to belong—while music remained her most delightful companion?"

10300220.m_mItemDesc3: "An astrolabe left at the convergence of realms. This intricate device helped the "alchemist" Seth transform oracles into symbols for study. In another life, would she ever find the power in her lifelong research to shape the world?"

10300230.m_mItemDesc3: "Ritual implements left at the convergence of realms. Essential tools for the "village witch" Dalcarlo to commune with spirits. In another life, would she have glimpsed an alternate fate—one where she became an elder in the castle—during her divinations?"

10300270.m_mItemDesc3: "A coffin left at the convergence of realms. The messy doodles on the wood are evidence of "queen of the playground" Piera leading her little friends into playful trouble. In another life, would she have indulged in an innocent childhood, free from the weight of carrying her family's burden?"

10300280.m_mItemDesc3: "A dirk left at the convergence of realms. This secret weapon accompanied Augustine the "Drifter" on countless missions during his life on the run. In another life, would he ponder the endless wandering through time and space as mere coincidences, or part of a greater design?"

10300290.m_mItemDesc3: "A timepiece left at the convergence of realms. This fractured device knew well how Aiona, the "chrono reverter," bent the flow of time to her will. In another life, would this extraordinarily gifted girl have found the ultimate answers to the universe through her countless experiments?"

10300300.m_mItemDesc3: "Fungi left at the convergence of realms. This radiant colony was carefully nurtured by Edina, the "fungal researcher." In another life, would she ever wonder about harmony between humanity and the wild as she wielded nature's power?"

10300310.m_mItemDesc3: "Webs left at the convergence of realms. Its eerie light was spun into illusions by the "magician" Pavana. In another life, would this master of illusions have known she too was caught in the weave of fate?"

10300330.m_mItemDesc3: "Blades left at the convergence of realms. Once, they were the lethal instruments of the "merciless blade" Nicole. In another life, would she still crave to dance beneath the moonlight, even stripped of dreams and humanity?"

10300340.m_mItemDesc3: "A plaguemask left at the convergence of realms. This precious relic was kept safe in a cabinet by "the town doctor" Thibault. In another life, where the plague never came, would she have found new meaning in the quiet practice of medicine?"

10300350.m_mItemDesc3: "A chariot left at the convergence of realms. Radiating golden brilliance, it was the vessel of Agares as the "Light Bearer," bestowing light and warmth. In another life, would he yearn for mortal pleasures as he traversed from sky to earth?"

10300370.m_mItemDesc3: "A spear left at the convergence of realms. Wrapped in bandages, this weapon bears witness to the countless triumphs over the Calamity by Tris, "the Bell Ringer of Glory." In another life, returning in triumph, would she live without regret?"

10300380.m_mItemDesc3: "A bow left at the convergence of realms. This bullhead crossbow witnessed the exceptional marksmanship of Selena, the "tribal hunter." In another life, embraced by the applause of her kin, would she have longed to embark on an unknown adventure?"

10300390.m_mItemDesc3: "A halberd left at the convergence of realms. Carrying the aura of sin, it belonged to Noah, the "Phantom of Death," who was consumed by the Calamity. In another life, burdened by curse, would he finally break free from the chains of fate?"

10300400.m_mItemDesc3: "Twin guns forgotten by time and space, adorned with beast-heads, the proudest creation by the "charming rascal" Van Helsing. In another life, as he reveled in joy and madness, would he finally encounter a worthy adversary?"

10300420.m_mItemDesc3: "A crown left at the convergence of realms. Black was the color for Joan, the "rebel." In another life, after toppling the old order, might she have chosen peace to claim her victory?"

10300430.m_mItemDesc3: "A boater hat left at the convergence of realms. This eerie relic bore witness to the rightful deaths bestowed by Ottavia, the "judge." In another life, would her devotion to her beliefs have tempered the hatred she held for her sister?"

10300450.m_mItemDesc3: "A butterfly knife left at the convergence of realms. Carrying the aura of sin, it belonged to Hati, the "vigil of plague," who sealed the Calamity within herself. In another life, after conquering the Calamity, would she have endured the excruciating pain caused by the Black Blood within?"

10300470.m_mItemDesc3: "Branches left at the convergence of realms. Seemingly ordinary, yet it was part of Yggdrasill, the "world tree." In another life, would he have remained detached from the world, or longed for power over it?"

10300480.m_mItemDesc3: "A jellyfish left at the convergence of realms. These red and black aquatic creatures were the cherished pets of Ami, the "head of Landis." In another life, as she led her family through the Calamity, would she have realized she unleashed a power that could be a curse?"

10300490.m_mItemDesc3: "A great axe forgotten by time and space. Its stunning color was meticulously crafted by a blacksmith for Baphomet, the "new noble." In another life, would this newly fashioned noble have discovered another way to protect his family's legacy?"

10300500.m_mItemDesc3: "A grave of swords left at the convergence of realms. In another life, where the Calamity never struck, and the "other gravekeeper" Clive never had the need to draw the great blade, would he have become friends with that silver-haired traveler?"

10300510.m_mItemDesc3: "A wolf head left at the convergence of realms. These brutal offerings were symbols of power for Clive Jr., the "alpha wolf." In another life, would he have found someone worthy of his absolute power to protect?"

10300520.m_mItemDesc3: "A crossbow left at the convergence of realms. Its unique design reflected the distinctive taste of the "seafaring tycoon" Goldland. In another life, unburdened by his duty to revive his family's name, would he find pure joy in the endless expanse of the ocean?"

10300570.m_mItemDesc3: "A pool of blood left at the convergence of realms. Its dark stench marked how Limine, the "Daughter of Dracula, " turned the land into a Crimson Blood Bath. In another life, would she find fulfillment in endless power and the immortality she sought, even after realizing her own ambitions?"

10300610.m_mItemDesc3: "A dagger forgotten by time and space. Aiona has crossed every timeline, witnessing the end of all things. In another life, would she still carry her family's burden after trying to leave fate behind?"

10300640.m_mItemDesc3: "The blood of a siren, left at the convergence of realms. Sirens gathered around her, collecting every drop that she shed. Her tears ran black, filled with longing for home. In that place where Sapphire Isle sank beneath the waves, for whom do her tears fall?"

10300650.m_mItemDesc3: "A noble's crossbow, left at the convergence of realms. The bow is exquisite, carved with lavish yet impractical decorations and patterns. More a display of wealth than a weapon. In that place where she became nobility, can she still recall her days of impoverishment?"

10300660.m_mItemDesc3: "A conch shell, left at the convergence of realms. The beautiful shell bears the marks of time and tide. In that place where she became a puppet, can she still recall the promise they made on the beach?"

10300700.m_mItemDesc3: "A Blood-Smeared Cloak, left at the convergence of realms. The scorch marks and bloodstains on the cloak tell tales of a brutal Holy War. In that place where she stands undefeated on the battlefield, does she ever long for peace?"

20100010.m_mItemDesc2: "Noah's Ultimate spawns 5 Blood Scythes that deal AoE DMG."
20100010.m_mItemDesc3: "A silver sword left at the convergence of realms. The blood crusted on its hilt speaks of Noah's glorious victories as the "Bloodborn hunter" for the Church. In another life, would he still suffer from doubt, or yearn for an unreachable homeland—even if he no longer dwelled in the shadow of the sun?"

20100020.m_mItemDesc2: "After Jestel releases her Ultimate, a Fire Emblem forms beneath her, dealing DMG every sec to enemies in range for a period of time. The DMG radius of her Ultimate is also increased."
20100020.m_mItemDesc3: "A shield left at the convergence of realms. Its twisted design was once hailed by the "great weaponsmith" Jestel as a work of rare artistry. In another life, would she still recall the tale of the Moonblessed, and share it with her kin?"

20100030.m_mItemDesc2: "The duration of Empousa's Ultimate is greatly extended and DMG area increased."
20100030.m_mItemDesc3: "A bouquet left at the convergence of realms. Planting carnations among piles of bones was the wish of Empousa, the "new leader of the family." In another life, would she wonder how fate might have shifted, had she dared venture into Starfall Valley that night?"

20100040.m_mItemDesc2: "Aiona's Ultimate grants All DMG Up (Moderate) and All DMG Taken Down (Moderate) to all allies in a select area."
20100040.m_mItemDesc3: "Observation equipment left at the convergence of realms. "The observer of time," Aiona, has worn through thousands like it. In another life, would she abandon her obsession with the end of time—and consider leaving the Alita family to seek a different sky?"

20100050.m_mItemDesc2: "Setti's Basic ATK gains 2 extra arrows, while her Ultimate gains 1, with the final strike firing 3 arrows.Both her Basic ATK and Ultimate can deal DMG to enemies in the way to the target, with each extra enemy hit increasing DMG dealt to the target by 10%."
20100050.m_mItemDesc3: "A flaming bow left at the convergence of realms. Its charred surface bears witness to the "new Bell Ringer" Setti’s mastery of fire. In another life, would she have questioned her teacher’s true intentions that night in Starfall Valley, after taking Agares's place?"

20100060.m_mItemDesc2: "When Ami releases her Ultimate, she forms a Soul Link with a Vassal who has not been Soul Linked before. The linked unit gains 30% of Ami's base ATK for 20 sec."
20100060.m_mItemDesc3: "Seafaring gourmet foods left at the convergence of realms. The writhing tentacles on the platter are trophies from Ami, "Captain of the El Dorado," taken from the deep. In another life, would she still yearn for the land while bound to the helm—or would the sea and storm, at last, feel like home?"

20100070.m_mItemDesc2: "Increases the bounce count of Cecia's Basic ATK and Ultimate to 8. Additionally, they can now hit allied summons, granting them ATK SPD UP (Minor). When more than 5 allied summons are present, her Ultimate releases an additional spirit head for every 2 additional allied summons."
20100070.m_mItemDesc3: "Bones left at the convergence of realms. Precisely modified and fused with the body of Cecia, the "Ascendant." In another life, having refused to be her family's sacrifice, would she have found her true self in flesh and metal?"

20100080.m_mItemDesc2: "Bella's Special can summon 2 extra Puppets, and her Ultimate can summon 3 extra Puppets, as well as 1 extra Joyce. The initial DMG and DMG area of Joyce's Ultimate are increased upon presence. And Joyce will continuously deal DMG to nearby enemies. Only 2 Joyce can be present."
20100080.m_mItemDesc3: "A music box left at the convergence of realms. The little girl dancing atop it glows like "Lady" Bella herself. In another life, as pure flesh and blood, would she care about if the puppet in the box had a soul?"

20100090.m_mItemDesc2: "Cain's Ultimate spawns 2 extra Rifts. Upon eliminating an enemy, there is a 10% chance to place an Insidious Delight at that location."
20100090.m_mItemDesc3: "A staff left at the convergence of realms. The snake coiled atop has guided countless lost souls with Cain, the "guide to the Other Side." In another life, when he walked the world of the living, would things have turned out differently for Cain had he finished that chess game at the Demon Banquet?"

20100100.m_mItemDesc2: "Agares' Ultimate triggers 2 extra explosions and creates a pool of flame that last for 5 sec, dealing M. DMG and inflicting Affliction to enemies in a circle."
20100100.m_mItemDesc3: "A torch left at the convergence of realms. Raising it was Agares's first act of feigned loyalty as "Dracula's follower." In another life, where he stands but one step from godhood, would he ever reminisce about the Manor of Eternal Flame?"

20100110.m_mItemDesc2: "Each Bounce from Lamia's Ultimate deals extra DMG to enemies in a small area around the target. While Blood Moon is active, Lamia also restores HP to all allies whenever her Ultimate defeats an enemy."
20100110.m_mItemDesc3: "Some bats forgotten by time and space, endlessly squabbling over food, carefree, like echoes of the newfound joy of Lamia, the "runaway." In another life, would she ever miss those petty battles at home after breaking free?"

20100120.m_mItemDesc2: "Gilrain's Ultimate summons 3 Raging Bulls and knocks back enemies in their way."
20100120.m_mItemDesc3: "A sword forgotten by time and space, one that has purged countless heretics, bestowed upon Gilrain by the Church when he was chosen as the "Bell Ringer of Light." In another life, no longer shying away from the light, would he secretly long for a worthy adversary?"

20100130.m_mItemDesc2: "Hati enters Bloodthirst at the start of battle. Both the radius of her Ultimate and Spectral Wolf Trap are greatly increased."
20100130.m_mItemDesc3: "A gauntlet left at the convergence of realms. The wolf claws on it were the prized weapons of Hati. In another life, no longer the "warrior of Ganelon," would she simply wear the cloak her father made and visit the town for the blooming Wolfsbane?"

20100140.m_mItemDesc2: "Spectral Gilrain's Ultimate can target any enemy on the field. Upon casting, Gilrain teleports behind the target and deals AoE DMG. If an enemy is eliminated, the skill can be cast again, and will target the farthest enemy. Each subsequent cast deals slightly reduced DMG, up to 3 additional times, upon which Gilrain returns to his original position. During his Ultimate, Gilrain deals DMG to all enemies along his path. Up to 5 Shadowy Apparitions can be present, who will also cast their Ultimate from their position at the same time as Gilrain."
20100140.m_mItemDesc3: "Shears left at the convergence of realms. In the hands of Gilrain, the "castle gardener," it became a tool for shearing sheep and tending to flowers. In another life, where peace is his sole pursuit, would he ever truly quench his hunger for power?"

20100150.m_mItemDesc2: "Mass's Ultimate has an increased DMG radius. When enemies are eliminated, Mass recovers HP and gradually reduces the Bloodsoul cost of her next Ultimate."
20100150.m_mItemDesc3: "A mantle left at the convergence of realms. The massive bat wings are a symbol of loyalty to Dracula as a "Bloodborn elder." In another life, would Mass move on from that palace after turning her back on the family?"

20100160.m_mItemDesc2: "Ressa's Ultimate now targets an enemy in range and pulls in surrounding enemies in a fan, dealing DMG to the target and Bounce DMG to surrounding enemies."
20100160.m_mItemDesc3: "A pair of handwraps left at the convergence of realms. The rose pattern adorning them symbolizes the happy ending of "village girl" Ressa with her childhood sweetheart. In another life, would she ever realize how precious her simple life on Sunset Isle was?"

20100170.m_mItemDesc2: "Darcias deals 50% increased DMG to enemies with Bloodthirst, and the radius of her Heavy Strike is greatly increased."
20100170.m_mItemDesc3: "Remains of beasts left at the convergence of realms. The precise cuts speak to the surgical mastery of the "bounty hunter" Darcias. In another life, would she look back on her pursuit of wealth as a quiet submission to a darker power?"

20100180.m_mItemDesc2: "Friedrich's Ultimate radius is increased. Upon gaining a Shield, deals 60% of the Shield value (P. DMG) to nearby enemies."
20100180.m_mItemDesc3: "A longsword left at the convergence of realms. Its unique design marks it as belonging to the second son of the Roland family—the Knight. In another life, freed from his fate as a Bell Ringer candidate, would Friedrich ever find his true calling?"

20100190.m_mItemDesc2: "Theophane's Ultimate now creates a Flaming Barrier with a greatly increased area. Enemies near the Flaming Barrier continuously take DMG."
20100190.m_mItemDesc3: "Decorations left at the convergence of realms. A shield-like statue bearing the crest of the deities, handpicked by the "humble dad" Theophane as a gift for his beloved daughter. In another life, would he simply savor the joy of family in a world untouched by war?"

20100200.m_mItemDesc2: "During Counterattack Stance, Gadric gains a Shield equal to 30% of his Max HP. When leaving Counterattack Stance, he swings at the target, inflicting a short Knockback."
20100200.m_mItemDesc3: "Snacks left at the convergence of realms. These black garlics were "tavern regular" Gadric's favorite delicacy during tavern nights with friends. In another life, would he have a lighter heart for such simple indulgences?"

20100210.m_mItemDesc2: "Acappella's Ultimate no longer consumes Bloodsoul, Ancient Aria provides enhanced buffs, and the healing effect of her Special is increased by 100%."
20100210.m_mItemDesc3: "A violin left at the convergence of realms. Bizarrely shaped, yet it served "dark nursery composer" Acappella best in crafting her works. In another life, wandering the streets without a home, would she still yearn for a place to belong—while music remained her most delightful companion?"

20100220.m_mItemDesc2: "Seth's Ultimate purifies all debuffs, reduces the ATK SPD of all enemies, and resets the stage failure counter."
20100220.m_mItemDesc3: "A chronometer left at the convergence of realms. This intricate device helped the "alchemist" Seth transform oracles into symbols for study. In another life, would she ever find the power in her lifelong research to shape the world?"

20100230.m_mItemDesc2: "Deals massive DMG to targets marked by Divination. Non-elite enemies marked by Divination are transformed into Dalcarlo's cats for an extended duration."
20100230.m_mItemDesc3: "Ritual implements left at the convergence of realms. Essential tools for the "village witch" Dalcarlo to commune with spirits. In another life, would she have glimpsed an alternate fate—one where she became an elder in the castle—during her divinations?"

20100270.m_mItemDesc2: "Piera's Tier 3 Spirit Bone Tower has more Bounces per Basic ATK and Slows enemies hit, while the duration is doubled."
20100270.m_mItemDesc3: "A coffin left at the convergence of realms. The messy doodles on the wood are evidence of "queen of the playground" Piera leading her little friends into playful trouble. In another life, would she have indulged in an innocent childhood, free from the weight of carrying her family's burden?"

20100280.m_mItemDesc2: "Augustine's Ultimate launches 2 extra chains to grab enemies."
20100280.m_mItemDesc3: "A dirk left at the convergence of realms. This secret weapon witnessed countless missions carried out by the "drifter" Augustine during his life on the run. In another life, would he ponder the endless wandering through time and place—mere coincidences, or part of a greater design?"

20100290.m_mItemDesc2: "Aiona applies a Force Field to allies with Shield, which continuously deals DMG to nearby enemies."
20100290.m_mItemDesc3: "A timepiece left at the convergence of realms. This fractured device knew well how Aiona, the "Sorceress of Time," bent the flow of time to her will. In another life, would this extraordinarily gifted girl have found the ultimate answers to the universe through her countless experiments?"

20100300.m_mItemDesc2: "Edina's Ultimate has an increased area and creates a field of flowers that continuously deals DMG and Slows enemies inside."
20100300.m_mItemDesc3: "Fungi left at the convergence of realms. This radiant colony was carefully nurtured by Edina, the "fungal researcher." In another life, would she ever wonder harmony between humanity and the wild as she wielded nature's power?"

20100310.m_mItemDesc2: "When Pavana's Ultimate lands, it releases her Special in all directions."
20100310.m_mItemDesc3: "Webs left at the convergence of realms. Its eerie light was spun into illusions by the "magician" Pavana. In another life, would this master of illusions have known she too was caught in the weave of fate?"

20100330.m_mItemDesc2: "Nicole's Ultimate has a wider radius and leaves mercury trails that last for a period of time, Slowing enemies that touch them."
20100330.m_mItemDesc3: "Blades left at the convergence of realms. Once, they were the lethal instruments of the "merciless blade" Nicole. In another life, would she still crave to dance beneath the moonlight, even stripped of dreams and humanity?"

20100340.m_mItemDesc2: "Thibault's Ultimate has a greatly increased channeling duration, with the radius of the storm gradually expanding over time and pulling enemies toward its eye."
20100340.m_mItemDesc3: "A plaguemask left at the convergence of realms. This precious relic was kept safe in a cabinet by "the town doctor" Thibault. In another life, where the plague never came, would she have found new meaning in the quiet practice of medicine?"

20100350.m_mItemDesc2: "When Incendiary Agares eliminates an enemy, CRIT DMG increases by 1%, up to a maximum of 300%. His Ultimate no longer changes direction, and deals DMG to enemies in a straight line."
20100350.m_mItemDesc3: "A chariot left at the convergence of realms. Radiating golden brilliance, it was the vessel of Agares as the "light bearer," bestowing light and warmth. In another life, would he yearn for mortal pleasures as he traversed from sky to earth?"

20100370.m_mItemDesc2: "Ultimate fires 6 extra electromagnetic arrows at random enemies near the target area. Each arrow deals AoE DMG and creates an electrical net."
20100370.m_mItemDesc3: "A spear left at the convergence of realms. Wrapped in bandages, this weapon bears witness to the countless triumphs over the Calamity by Tris, "the Bell Ringer of Glory." In another life, returning in triumph, would she live without regret?"

20100380.m_mItemDesc2: "When Selena's Ultimate hits, each Shadow Arrow consumed will transform into a piercing arrow that scatters in all directions, dealing DMG to enemies in its path."
20100380.m_mItemDesc3: "A bow left at the convergence of realms. This bullhead crossbow witnessed the exceptional marksmanship of Selena, the "tribal hunter." In another life, embraced by the applause of her kin, would she have longed to embark on an unknown adventure?"

20100390.m_mItemDesc2:
"Shade limit increased to 10. When a Shade dissipates, it releases two Wormholes.
When Noha's Ultimate eliminates an enemy, it creates a Spirit Shade that attacks automatically. Up to 10 can exist simultaneously. Upon death or expiration they Self-Destruct and deal AoE DMG."
20100390.m_mItemDesc3: "A halberd left at the convergence of realms. Carrying the aura of sin, it belonged to Noah, the "phantom Death," who was consumed by the Calamity. In another life, burdened by the curse, would he finally break free from the chain of fate?"

20100400.m_mItemDesc2: "Van Helsing's Basic ATK and the attacks following his Ultimate fire two extra piercing shots on either side of the target."
20100400.m_mItemDesc3: "Twin guns forgotten by time and space, adorned with beast-heads, the proudest creation by the "charming rascal" Van Helsing. In another life, as he reveled in joy and madness, would he finally encounter a worthy adversary?"

20100420.m_mItemDesc2: "If Electrified during her Ultimate, Joan creates a Lightning Storm that deals weak P. DMG to enemies in a circle every sec and applies Zap to them."
20100420.m_mItemDesc3: "A crown left at the convergence of realms. Black was the color for Joan, the "rebel." In another life, after toppling the old order, might she have chosen peace to claim her victory?"

20100430.m_mItemDesc2: "Ottavia's Ultimate instantly executes enemies below 30% of their Max HP. The cooldown of her Special has changed to 1 sec, and when triggered, deals DMG to all surrounding enemies."
20100430.m_mItemDesc3: "A boater hat left at the convergence of realms. This eerie relic bore witness to the rightful deaths bestowed by Ottavia, the "judge." In another life, would her devotion to her beliefs have tempered the hatred she held for her sister?"

20100450.m_mItemDesc2: "Transcendent Hati no longer performs Basic ATK, and instead continuously casts her Special."
20100450.m_mItemDesc3: "A butterfly knife left at the convergence of realms. Carrying the aura of sin, it belonged to Hati, the "Plague Bearer," who sealed the Calamity within herself. In another life, after conquering the Calamity, would she have endured the excruciating pain caused by the Black Blood within?"

20100470.m_mItemDesc2: "Yggdrasill's Green Grotto increases in size, and when created it knocks back nearby enemies outside, while Slowing any enemies inside."
20100470.m_mItemDesc3: "Branches left at the convergence of realms. Seemingly ordinary, yet it was part of Yggdrasill, the "world tree." In another life, would he have remained detached from the world, or longed for power over it?"

20100480.m_mItemDesc2: "Ranna's Ultimate now creates larger waves that push enemies back and deal increased DMG."
20100480.m_mItemDesc3: "A jellyfish left at the convergence of realms. These red and black aquatic creatures were the cherished pets of Ami, the "head of Landis." In another life, as she led her family through the Calamity, would she have realized she unleashed a power that could be a curse?"

20100490.m_mItemDesc2: "Baphomet's Special now triggers every 2 Basic ATKs, has increased range, and deals higher DMG to enemies at the center of its area."
20100490.m_mItemDesc3: "A great axe forgotten by time and space. Its stunning color was meticulously crafted by a blacksmith for Baphomet, the "new noble." In another life, would this newly fashioned noble have discovered another way to protect his family's legacy?"

20100500.m_mItemDesc2: "Ultimate now launches more Wolf Spirits in a select direction."
20100500.m_mItemDesc3: "A grave of swords left at the convergence of realms. In another life, where the Calamity never struck, and the "other gravekeeper" Clive never had the need to draw the great blade, would he have become friends with that silver-haired traveler?"

20100510.m_mItemDesc2: "Clive Jr.'s Special summons one extra Werewolf, while his Ultimate summons two extra Werewolves, while also summoning Clive."
20100510.m_mItemDesc3: "A wolf head left at the convergence of realms. These brutal offerings were symbols of power for Clive Jr., the "alpha wolf." In another life, would he have found someone worthy of his absolute power to protect?"

20100520.m_mItemDesc2: "Goldland's Special now automatically activates once every 40 sec."
20100520.m_mItemDesc3: "A crossbow left at the convergence of realms. Its unique design reflected the distinctive taste of the "seafaring tycoon" Goldland. In another life, unburdened by his duty to revive his family's name, would he find pure joy in the endless expanse of the ocean?"

20100570.m_mItemDesc2: "Ultimate creates a Blood Pool at the target location that slows enemies, then explodes after a short period, dealing DMG."
20100570.m_mItemDesc3: "A hunting ground left at the convergence of realms. Its eerie scent of blood marked how Limine, the "Dracula's daughter, " turned the land into a bloodbath. In another life, would she find fulfillment in the endless power and immortality she sought, after realizing her ambitions?"

20100610.m_mItemDesc2: "During her Ultimate duration, Timeless Aiona's Basic ATK can target additional enemies."
20100610.m_mItemDesc3: "A dagger forgotten by time and space. Aiona has crossed every timeline, witnessing the end of all things. In another life, would she still carry her family's burden after trying to leave fate behind?"

20100640.m_mItemDesc2: "In her Siren Form, Lorelei deals cone-shaped AoE damage with both her Basic Attack and Special."
20100640.m_mItemDesc3: "The blood of a siren, left at the convergence of realms. Sirens gathered around her, collecting every drop that she shed. Her tears ran black, filled with longing for home. In that place where Sapphire Isle sank beneath the waves, for whom do her tears fall?"

20100650.m_mItemDesc2: "Jinxed Selena's Ultimate updated: Observes enemies in a select range, dealing DMG to all enemies within the area."
20100650.m_mItemDesc3: "A noble's crossbow, left at the convergence of realms. The bow is exquisite, carved with lavish yet impractical decorations and patterns. More a display of wealth than a weapon. In that place where she became nobility, can she still recall her days of impoverishment?"

20100660.m_mItemDesc2: "When possessed by Fleeting Bella, both instance of extra DMG and DMG dealt increase for Basic ATK."
20100660.m_mItemDesc3: "A conch shell, left at the convergence of realms. The beautiful shell bears the marks of time and tide. In that place where she became a puppet, can she still recall the promise they made on the beach?"

20100700.m_mItemDesc2: "If Sirene has Dark Intentions, she will only use her Special and releases an additional shadowed spirit at a random enemy for each stack of Festering Desire she has."
20100700.m_mItemDesc3: "A Blood-Smeared Cloak, left at the convergence of realms. The scorch marks and bloodstains on the cloak tell tales of a brutal Holy War. In that place where she stands undefeated on the battlefield, does she ever long for peace?"

20200001.m_mItemDesc3: "A dark, bitter liquid that keeps one alert through the night. Would likely fetch a good price among night watchmen and ascetics."
20200001.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 1"

20200003.m_mItemDesc2: "All Melee units now deal DMG in a cone. This effect has a probability of dealing DMG two additional times."
20200003.m_mItemDesc3: "A weapon that fits in the palm. When unfolded, it becomes a fan with razor edges. Favored by eastern assassins, it reaps souls in silence."

20200004.m_mItemDesc2: "All Melee units create Blood Pools around them. Enemies entering the pools take DMG while the unit recovers HP. Increases range, DMG, and Lifesteal."
20200004.m_mItemDesc3: "A syringe with silver spikes. In the hands of The Peace Council, it would be a perfect instrument for drawing blood."

20200005.m_mItemDesc2: "Enemies have a chance to explode upon death. The explosion radius is increased, dealing extra DMG equal to 10% of the monster's Max HP to all nearby enemies."
20200005.m_mItemDesc3: "A container filled with black powder brought from the east by the El Dorado. A single spark is enough to unleash earth-shattering power."

20200006.m_mItemDesc2: "A chance to trigger a chain lightning effect on up to 3 targets, upon hitting enemies with ranged Basic ATKs. Increased trigger chance, +3 targets, each with a chance for secondary."
20200006.m_mItemDesc3:
"A glasswork device, handcrafted with care.
Someone once tried to trap light inside—only to catch a fleeting rainbow instead."
20200006.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 7"

20200007.m_mItemDesc2: "All Sorcerers and Enchanters have a chance to create a meteor when using Basic ATK, dealing AoE DMG in a random area, with increased trigger chance and meteor radius and greatly increased DMG, and leaves a burning effect."
20200007.m_mItemDesc3: "A flaming rock fell from the sky. Is it Aeon's divine punishment, or a harbinger of disaster?"
20200007.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 2"

20200008.m_mItemDesc2: "All Marksmen are accompanied by a Wooden Aerocraft. Increases number of Wooden Aerocrafts."
20200008.m_mItemDesc3: "A peculiar wooden device that lifts one up in the sky. One shudders to think what eccentrics the Hermetic Order might make with it."

20200009.m_mItemDesc2: "When enemies approach the rift, causes turbulence that deals massive DMG to all enemies and knocks them back."
20200009.m_mItemDesc3: "A stone altar adorned with candlelight, surrounded by beast heads. Is it a magic circle, or a heretic's sacrifice?"
20200009.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 4"

20200013.m_mItemDesc2: "Periodically places a barrel at random locations on the field. The barrel explodes when enemies make contact, dealing AoE DMG and leaving a burning effect."
20200013.m_mItemDesc3: "A barrel filled with the nectar of joy. A single taste of euphoria, enough to intoxicate and ease sleepless nights."
20200013.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 6"

20200015.m_mItemDesc3: "An insect with a demonic appearance. It explodes when startled, releasing repulsive fumes. A true creation of the abyss."

20200016.m_mItemDesc3: "A tissue that binds mother and child. The sisters of the Peace Council deem it a vessel of life, often crafting it into amulets."

20200017.m_mItemDesc2: "Periodically place an ice trap at random locations that continuously slow nearby enemies and deal DMG. Freezes enemies when hitting a certain speed."
20200017.m_mItemDesc3: "A clay instrument with small holes. When the right tune is played, strange phenomena seem to awaken."
20200017.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 5"

20200018.m_mItemDesc3: "A defensive structure. It's the final line of defense against enemies."

20200019.m_mItemDesc3: "A barricade armed with sharp barbs, a strong defense to ward off Blood Beasts."

20200020.m_mItemDesc2: "All melee units create a circling fireball that launches upon hitting an enemy, dealing DMG to enemies in its path. Increased fireballs to three and DMG dealt."
20200020.m_mItemDesc3:
"A complex mechanical device.
Inspired by an engineer's nightmare, some speculated he dreamed of hellfire raining from the sky.
In fact, it was just a dream about complicated parabolic formulas."
20200020.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 8"

20300001.m_mItemDesc2: "Card skill that deals fixed AoE DMG in a select area. Initial energy cost is 8, but reduces by 1 for every 20 monsters eliminated, while increasing DMG."
20300001.m_mItemDesc3: "A peculiar device prone to sudden explosions. In the wrong hands, the consequences are unthinkable."
20300001.m_mUnlockText: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 3"
